==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg-both}}

# {{uncountable}} A kind of drama having a musical accompaniment to intensify the effect of certain scenes (archaic).
# {{countable}} A drama abounding in romantic sentiment and agonizing situations, with a musical accompaniment only in parts which are especially thrilling or pathetic. In opera, a passage in which the orchestra plays a somewhat descriptive accompaniment, while the actor speaks; as, the melodrama in the gravedigging scene of Beethoven's "Fidelio".

